<header class="header">
  <h1>Pollination Bags vs Organza Bags for Seed Saving</h1>
  <p class="tagline">
    Both can isolate flowers, but they’re not designed for exactly the same purpose.
  </p>
  <p class="lede">
    <strong>For most gardeners, organza bags work well for seed saving, while dedicated pollination bags offer more reliable insect exclusion and durability.</strong>
  </p>
  <p>
    Seed saving requires preventing cross-pollination, especially when growing multiple varieties. The right type of bag helps isolate flowers while still allowing airflow and normal plant development.
  </p>
  <p>
    Pollination bags and organza bags are often used interchangeably, but they perform differently in real conditions.
  </p>
